---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro'
const lastUpdated = '2026-06-10'
---

<Base
  title="Affiliate Disclosure"
  description="FTC-compliant affiliate disclosure for Pilot.BM. Current affiliate relationships, the /go/ redirect system, and how sponsorship affects (and does not affect) our coverage."
>
  <section style="background-color: var(--color-sand); padding-block: var(--space-10);">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: var(--text-3xl);">Affiliate Disclosure</h1>
      <p style="color: var(--color-muted); font-size: var(--text-sm);">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container" style="padding-block: var(--space-12);">
    <div style="max-width: 720px;" class="prose">

      <h2>FTC disclosure</h2>
      <p>
        In accordance with the U.S. Federal Trade Commission (FTC) guidelines (16 C.F.R. Part 255),
        Pilot.BM discloses that some links on this website are affiliate links.
        When you click an affiliate link and make a qualifying purchase, Pilot.BM may receive
        a commission from the affiliate partner at no additional cost to you.
      </p>

      <h2>How affiliate links work on this site</h2>
      <p>
        Affiliate links on Pilot.BM route through our <code>/go/</code> redirect system.
        For example, <code>pilot.bm/go/oleander-cycles</code> redirects to Oleander Cycles' website.
        The <code>/go/</code> path:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Makes affiliate links clearly identifiable</li>
        <li>Allows us to track referral volume (aggregated, no personal data)</li>
        <li>Routes to the fallback direct URL when an affiliate programme is pending approval</li>
        <li>Is labelled with <code>rel="nofollow sponsored"</code> per Google's link guidelines</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Current active affiliate relationships</h2>
      <p>
        As of {lastUpdated}, <strong>no affiliate programmes are yet active</strong> on Pilot.BM.
        We have applied to the following networks and are pending approval (networks have a 4–8 week
        review period before commissions begin):
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>GetYourGuide</strong> — Bermuda tours and activities (pending)</li>
        <li><strong>Viator</strong> — Bermuda activities (pending)</li>
        <li><strong>Booking.com via CJ/Awin</strong> — hotel search (pending)</li>
        <li><strong>OpenTable</strong> — restaurant reservations (pending)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Until programmes are approved and links are activated, <code>/go/</code> redirects use direct
        fallback URLs (non-affiliate links). This page will be updated when programmes go live.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Oleander Cycles</strong> (<code>/go/oleander-cycles</code>) is a direct non-affiliate link.
        We include it as a convenience link only.
      </p>

      <h2>Directory tiers</h2>
      <p>
        Pilot.BM's business directory includes paid listing tiers (Standard at $30/mo,
        Featured at $50/mo, Anchor at $100/mo). These are commercial arrangements —
        businesses pay for enhanced placement, photos, and partner badges.
        Paid listings are clearly labelled with their tier badge and "Pilot.BM Partner" designation.
      </p>
      <p>
        Payment for a directory listing does not influence our editorial coverage or the content
        of our guides. We will not write favourably about a business in our editorial content
        because they have a paid directory listing.
      </p>

      <h2>Editorial independence</h2>
      <p>
        Affiliate relationships and directory fees do not influence our editorial content.
        We will recommend a non-affiliate option if it genuinely serves the reader better.
        When a sponsored or affiliate option is the genuine recommendation, we will say so.
      </p>

      <h2>Questions</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about our affiliate relationships or disclosure:
        <a href="mailto:matt@ravenpower.net">matt@ravenpower.net</a>
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
